[6] Australia (Brisbane): 3 cases, 1 ex Mozambique
Date: Wed 16 Oct 2019
Source: The Age [abridged, edited]
https://www.theage.com.au/national/queensland/unprecedented-measles-outbreak-on-brisbane-s-south-triggers-warning-20191016-p531cy.html


An unprecedented outbreak of measles in Brisbane's south has triggered an urgent plea by Metro South Health for people to get checked and vaccinated. Eight cases of measles were detected in the past few weeks, with public health physician Dr Kari Jarvinen expecting many more cases to arise.

"There are well over 1000 contacts (people who could be affected) that we know about and there will be more, and the numbers are increasing even today as we speak when we find out more information," he said.

Dr Jarvinen said one child was infectious during a flight from Auckland to Brisbane, while some others caused a potential spread in a college. [See URL for locations / times of possible exposure. - Mod.LK]

Dr Jarvinen said the number of cases was highly unusual, especially in the southeast Queensland area.

"In our area, we might see 1-3 cases a year," he said. "In the last few years, we have had similar numbers or more, but this is fairly unprecedented . . . getting so many cases so quickly. Very rarely we will see 2 or 3 cases linked occasionally, but not like this.

"Many of these are closely related through family and social connections and networks, but it's also beyond that.

"We fully expect the numbers to increase, because quite a large number of people have been exposed to measles while these people have been infectious."

[Byline: Jocelyn Garcia]

