[7] Australia (Queensland (Cairns and Mission Bay))
Date: Fri 25 Oct 2019
https://www.gladstoneobserver.com.au/news/new-measles-cases-suspected-in-far-north/3863003/


Two more measles cases are likely to be confirmed in the Far North, as an outbreak of the vaccine-preventable disease threatens to spread further across the region.

Public health officials have urged people who are unvaccinated to be immunised immediately, and to be alert for symptoms to prevent a wider outbreak of the infectious disease, following 2 new suspected cases emerging in Cairns and Mission Beach.

To date, there has been 3 cases of measles confirmed across the region since 3 Oct [2019].

Tropical Public Health Services director Dr Richard Gair said one of the latest cases, who lived at Mission Beach, was unknowingly infectious and visited Malanda [Queensland] on the weekend of 19-20 Oct [2019]. The other suspected case is from Cairns.

"If these cases are confirmed, it will bring the total number of cases of measles in the Cairns region to 5 in the last few weeks," Dr Gair said.

[Byline: Daniel Bateman]

